<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">n</emphasis>
= 42, 60, 62, 63, 63-64, 78, 84. The one 2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">n</emphasis>
= 42 count was originally published by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1537-2197.1946.tb12904.x" author="Hartung, ME" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" pagination="516 - 531" refId="B14" refString="Hartung, ME, 1946. Chromosome numbers in Poa, Agropyron and Elymus. American Journal of Botany 33 (6): 516 - 531, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1537-2197.1946.tb12904.x" title="Chromosome numbers in Poa, Agropyron and Elymus." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1537-2197.1946.tb12904.x" volume="33" year="1946">Hartung (1946)</bibRefCitation>
